#X text 1162 142 # EXPLANATION OF WHY FOR DISCRETE-FREQUENCY-INDEX(DFI) OR K0 = 3.5 \, THERE IS NOT REAL PART TO FFT AND ALL IMAGINARY: \; THIS IS DUE TO THE ODD SYMMETRY OF \$0-input. CONSIDER IN DFT/FFT \, REAL(COSINE) PART OF THE EXAMINER FUNCTION FOR EVERY BIN (0 TO 63) \, WILL BE MULTIPLIED BY \$0-input TO FIND CORRELATION. NOW SINCE "EXAMINER COSINES" ALL WILL HAVE EVEN SYMMETRY AT 64/2 \, THE MULTIPLICATION OF ANY OF THE EXAMINER COSINES BY \$0-input WILL SUM TO 0 -> NO CORRELATION! \; # MATHEMATICAL EXPLANATION OF NON-INTEGER INPUT SINUSOID TO FFT: THE VIDEO LECTURE 206-1b (1:00) OF 206.18s AND THE BOOK ARE SHIT -> FIND BETTER SOURCE IF INTERESTED \; # GREAT INTUITION FROM CONVERSATION WITH CHATGPT ABOUT THIS AND RELATION TO SINC FUNCTION: https://chatgpt.com/g/g-p-68fa638800408191a563a8262a1493d8-pd-music-programming/c/69c250ce-2f08-8326-ba58-dbb3851f545e, f 75;
